Sec. 13.452. DEVICE MAINTENANCE ACTIVITIES. A person performs
device maintenance activities if the person or the person's employee:
(1) places a commercial weighing or measuring device in
service;
(2) installs, calibrates, or repairs a commercial weighing
or measuring device; or
(3) removes an out-of-order tag, stop-sale order, security
seal, lock, condemnation notice, or other form of use prohibition
placed on a weighing or measuring device by the department.

Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

